From: Leon Hwang <leon.hwang@linux.dev>
Date: Wed, 10 Sep 2025 20:57:39 +0800
Subject: bpf: Reject bpf_timer for PREEMPT_RT
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc6
Git-commit: e25ddfb388c8b7e5f20e3bf38d627fb485003781
References: git-fixes

When enable CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT, the kernel will warn when run timer
selftests by './test_progs -t timer':

BUG: sleeping function called from invalid context at kernel/locking/spinlock_rt.c:48

In order to avoid such warning, reject bpf_timer in verifier when
PREEMPT_RT is enabled.

Signed-off-by: Leon Hwang <leon.hwang@linux.dev>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250910125740.52172-2-leon.hwang@linux.dev
Signed-off-by: Alexei Starovoitov <ast@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 kernel/bpf/verifier.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
+++ b/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
@@ -7640,6 +7640,10 @@ static int process_timer_func(struct bpf
 		verbose(env, "verifier bug. Two map pointers in a timer helper\n");
 		return -EFAULT;
 	}
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT)) {
+		verbose(env, "bpf_timer cannot be used for PREEMPT_RT.\n");
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
+	}
 	meta->map_uid = reg->map_uid;
 	meta->map_ptr = map;
 	return 0;
